\p
\v 9 Wherefore I will yet plead with you, saith the LORD, and with your
children’s children will I plead. 
\v 10 For pass over the isles of Chittim, and see; and send unto Kedar, and
consider diligently, and see if there be such a thing. 
\v 11 Hath a nation changed \add their\add* gods, which \add are\add* yet no
gods? but my people have changed their glory for \add that which\add* doth not
profit. 
\v 12 Be astonished, O ye heavens, at this, and be horribly afraid, be ye very
desolate, saith the LORD. 
\v 13 For my people have committed two evils; they have forsaken me the
