Arise, and save us. 
\v 28 But where \add are\add* thy gods that thou hast made thee? let them
arise, if they can save thee in the time of thy trouble: for \add according
to\add* the number of thy cities are thy gods, O Judah. 
\v 29 Wherefore will ye plead with me? ye all have transgressed against me,
saith the LORD. 
\v 30 In vain have I smitten your children; they received no correction: your
own sword hath devoured your prophets, like a destroying lion.
\p
\v 31 O generation, see ye the word of the LORD. Have I been a wilderness unto
Israel? a land of darkness? wherefore say my people, We are lords; we will
