\v 26 I beheld, and, lo, the fruitful place \add was\add* a wilderness, and
all the cities thereof were broken down at the presence of the LORD, 
\add and\add* by his fierce anger. 
\v 27 For thus hath the LORD said, The whole land shall be desolate; yet will
I not make a full end. 
\v 28 For this shall the earth mourn, and the heavens above be black: because
I have spoken \add it,\add* I have purposed \add it,\add* and will not repent,
