\v 29 The whole city shall flee for the noise of the horsemen and bowmen; they
shall go into thickets, and climb up upon the rocks: every city \add shall be
\add* forsaken, and not a man dwell therein. 
\v 30 And \add when\add* thou \add art\add* spoiled, what wilt thou do? Though
thou clothest thyself with crimson, though thou deckest thee with ornaments of
gold, though thou rentest thy face with painting, in vain shalt thou make
